      "message": "From my understanding, the expected behavior of \"-gpu on\" is to create a sub-window on the host side, translate the GL commands and render to the sub-window. \"-gpu off\" will let the guest do software rendering and copy the framebuffer to the host. \"-gpu mesa\" shall behave the same as \"-gpu on\" except for the translator. But mesa does not create sub-window and instead sets up the gpu_frame_set_post_callback.",
